%N A094397 Numbers k such that k divides the (k+1)st Lucas number.
%H A094397 Chai Wah Wu, <a href="/A094397/b094397.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..411</a> (terms 1..185 from Charles R Greathouse IV)
%t A094397 Do[If[Mod[Fibonacci[n] + Fibonacci[n+2], n] == 0, Print[n]], {n, 1, 120000}] (* _Ryan Propper_, Jun 20 2005 *)
%o A094397 (PARI) is(n)=(Mod([0,1;1,1],n)^(n+1)*[2;1])[1,1]==0 \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Nov 04 2016
%o A094397 (Python)
%o A094397 from itertools import count, islice
%o A094397 from oeis_sequences.OEISsequences import lucas_mod
%o A094397 def A094397_gen(startvalue=1): # generator of terms >= startvalue
%o A094397     return filter(lambda k: not lucas_mod(k+1,k),count(max(startvalue,1)))
%o A094397 A094397_list = list(islice(A094397_gen(),20)) # _Chai Wah Wu_, Jul 15 2026
%Y A094397 Cf. A094396.
